    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a clear primary catalyst in **Gunnar Henderson** (81.17), who stands as our highest-projected asset. His upside is amplified by a favorable matchup against the right-handed S. Smith, but the true analytical edge lies in the opponent's \"Slow SP Delivery\" profile, which projects to boost **Gunnar Henderson**\u2019s stolen base probability to 93%\u2014a massive ceiling factor given our league\u2019s premium on speed. **Josh Lowe** (72.21) and **Nolan Schanuel** (67.16) also grade out as strong plays, capitalizing on a soft matchup against R. L\u00f3pez, whose 6.36 xERA provides a significant efficiency floor boost for our bats. **Kyle Tucker** (67.84) remains a mandatory start despite facing a competent arm in Gausman, as his projected volume at the #2 spot and dynamic platoon advantage stabilize his output.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today was excluding **Miguel Vargas** (49.69) from the active lineup. He narrowly missed the cut behind **Jackson Merrill** (51.82) and **Luis Robert Jr.** (50.76); while **Miguel Vargas** boasts a solid profile against the left-handed Tr. Rogers, his current efficiency projection simply didn't provide the requisite ceiling to displace our starters in a crowded outfield and utility landscape. We are keeping a close eye on **Jackson Merrill** as he faces Skenes; while his platoon edge is positive, the risk of facing an elite arm with an elite pitch-framing catcher (1.89s pop time) lowers his floor, making him a volatile piece of today\u2019s puzzle. We remain cautious with **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (52.89) against Yamamoto, where a tough SP skill rating and neutral park factors have muted his base projection, though he remains in the lineup due to his high baseline talent level.",
